[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating ClassLoader setup**\n\nI'm considering whether to test class resources in a native image. It seems better to create a temporary directory with a parent ClassLoader using URLClassLoader, pointing to the directory containing the resources. The child class loader can be empty, and this way, the parent can fetch filesystem resources. I wonder about the support for URLClassLoader in a native image, especially since Kafka uses it. I'll explore if the parent can get resources through the temp URLClassLoader, along with triggering and enumeration.\n\n**Reviewing test coverage**\n\nI see that line 82 can actually be addressed without needing a non-null branch, and that the report call site is the findLoadedClass call. The resource test will hit line 105 only if findResource is null, which is good. I need to ensure that line 113 will call getParent().getResources as long as parent is non-null. I wonder if I should include tests for public methods too, since all top-level test classes should be public. I might need to inspect dynamic coverage to verify that the class file is absent.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_082a49a7d750fe0b0169f2bc2881ec81908b601bf3bb283013\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8rw8dJ0evTao-zayjdyes8xo1GHdYyXk72GkDKmOg-NmRLIK_1d3S5YYIOykZDVMhmL9TcwEHgCG6P-E13gtBrq7zE6CtC9rSfu87KtZ-b_ZsbBAG37xnGr5JNyrWzuQ8FopJ9_UbdVgiAjofCvkd_lQAddnq0OCFPIeBVjt1dfKPmEzSTuz0MQtB5jCWsj39FBz-0SuWel-JreZqWwsu_W7Yqd1mhpRyxOqRovZ-grCxImPMe3UpG2Y_gTEqfWP7vKM_xZDi2iSClL_l-FgwVrCKCbHfWvQaP5DF0v2_Vxm1B3z8UwbMh7HlcSWbL0K8VVRbqV7JbfT4_qczn0TixmpIV-2JxZxg2Z8ApopO0bxVM8owOHo2bRla1OA_OPkFqWH3bthKs9kAMGNKEDAk8b9Q922R8HTxhi1pMvGpXiekI-cqkAs-5HFF_Rkb5FDxA4EhivZ4wSPwKJtfuF5tHApcuJeqvZ9gQZMq2YuHAEJJIESyYU_Cn7fwZEHwbu2h0Xx9eiwc9OwtWvjZFLezbm5ZO5i7cUuMM0FQRg_hfUB6IujZVoQYD6UHgSmZBu7WeAYxxifUM2Dxzwxxyyks0ADqT4HAKkeda-gvZSh_rmKul6Hfu7qmVla4RGmUMDQUOk